{"id":"cue-wtc","title":"Fix account variable current value so repeat panel expands per account","description":"The account variable current is set to {} which lets Grafana restore old session state (single-value "All"), causing the repeat panel to render once as "Utilization Over Time — All" instead of once per account.

Fix: set current to the multi-select array format so Grafana expands $__all to individual account values for the repeat:
```json
"current": {
  "selected": true,
  "text": ["All"],
  "value": ["$__all"]
}
```

Keep includeAll: false and multi: true as-is. The array format for text/value is what tells Grafana to expand to individual values for panel repeat rather than render a single "All" instance.","status":"open","priority":1,"issue_type":"bug","owner":"graeme@graemef.dev","created_at":"2026-03-03T17:03:26Z","created_by":"mayor","updated_at":"2026-03-03T17:03:26Z"}

